  "text": "A model of stratified care that uses information on the risk of persistent disabling non-specific LBP (prognostic risk: low, medium, high) and targets treatment accordingly, has been shown to be superior to non-stratified primary care [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The approach uses a brief self-report tool -the STarT Back tool [CITATION_3] which was developed for, and validated with, primary care patients with nonspecific LBP (with and without leg pain). A similar model of stratified care may be beneficial for sciatica patients consulting in primary care, but evidence is lacking.",
